<name>SUSPENSION &amp; AXLE</name>
<section id="1002H_S000J" variety="S000J">
<name>AXLE</name>
<ttl id="1002H_S000J_7A802_T004G" variety="T004G">
<name>REAR AXLE SHAFT</name>
<para id="RM000000ZZW00IX" category="G" type-id="8000T" name-id="AH02U-04" from="201202">
<name>ON-VEHICLE INSPECTION</name>
<subpara id="RM000000ZZW00IX_01" type-id="01" category="01">
<s-1 id="RM000000ZZW00IX_01_0001" proc-id="RM21Q0EV__00001IA00000">
<ptxt>CHECK REAR AXLE SHAFT BEARING</ptxt>
<content1 releasenbr="1">
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="F050086E01" width="2.775699831in" height="1.771723296in"/>
</figure>
<s2>
<ptxt>Remove the rear wheel.</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>Remove the brake drum.</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>Inspect the axle shaft backlash.</ptxt>
<s3>
<ptxt>Using a dial indicator, check the backlash near the center of the axle shaft.</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>Maximum backlash</title>
<specitem>
<ptxt>0.5 mm (0.0197 in.)</ptxt>
</specitem>
</spec>
<ptxt>If the backlash is greater than the maximum, replace the bearing.</ptxt>
</s3>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>Inspect the axle shaft deviation.</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="F050085E01" width="2.775699831in" height="1.771723296in"/>
</figure>
<s3>
<ptxt>Using a dial indicator, check the deviation at the surface of the axle shaft.</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>Maximum deviation</title>
<specitem>
<ptxt>0.1 mm (0.0039 in.)</ptxt>
</specitem>
</spec>
<ptxt>If the deviation is greater than the maximum, replace the bearing.</ptxt>
</s3>
</s2>
</content1>
</s-1>
</subpara>
</para>
</ttl>
</section>
</servcat>
</pub>
